H$_2$ H–H 0.245 -1.08 0
Li$_2$ Li–Li 0.013 +0.02 0
N$_2$ N≡N 0.715 -3.65 0
O$_2$ O=O 0.515 -1.56 0
F$_2$ F–F 0.245 +0.15 0

Note: F$_2$ has a positive Laplacian despite being covalent—this indicates the bond is weak and the charge depletion between nuclei is characteristic of its repulsive nature.

Hydrogen bond in water dimer:

At the O···H BCP: $\rho_b \approx 0.02$ au, $\nabla^2 \rho_b \approx +0.10$ au — typical for hydrogen bonds (closed-shell interaction).

