Chemistry is far from complete. The open problems in this part—protein folding, artificial photosynthesis, programmable matter, homochirality, single‑molecule dynamics, assembly theory—are the frontiers where the next generation will build. The equations we have are powerful, but they are also approximations. Deeper understanding will require new mathematics, new experiments, and new ways of thinking.

