Appendix M — Computational Chemistry Methods

M.1 Hartree-Fock Method

The Hartree-Fock equations are:

\hat{F} \phi_i = \epsilon_i \phi_i

where the Fock operator is:

\hat{F}(1) = \hat{h}(1) + \sum_{j=1}^N [\hat{J}_j(1) - \hat{K}_j(1)]

with:

· Core Hamiltonian: $\hat{h}(1) = -\frac{1}{2}\nabla_1^2 - \sum_A \frac{Z_A}{r_{1A}}$
· Coulomb operator: $\hat{J}_j(1) \phi_i(1) = \left[ \int \phi_j^*(2) \frac{1}{r_{12}} \phi_j(2) d\tau_2 \right] \phi_i(1)$
· Exchange operator: $\hat{K}_j(1) \phi_i(1) = \left[ \int \phi_j^*(2) \frac{1}{r_{12}} \phi_i(2) d\tau_2 \right] \phi_j(1)$

The Hartree-Fock energy is:

E_{\text{HF}} = \sum_i \langle i | \hat{h} | i \rangle + \frac{1}{2} \sum_{i,j} (\langle ij | ij \rangle - \langle ij | ji \rangle)

M.2 Post-Hartree-Fock Methods

Møller-Plesset perturbation theory (MP2):

E_{\text{MP2}} = E_{\text{HF}} + \sum_{i<j} \sum_{a<b} \frac{|\langle ij || ab \rangle|^2}{\epsilon_i + \epsilon_j - \epsilon_a - \epsilon_b}

Coupled Cluster (CCSD):

|\Psi_{\text{CC}}\rangle = e^{\hat{T}} |\Phi_0\rangle

where $\hat{T} = \hat{T}_1 + \hat{T}_2 + \cdots$ with $\hat{T}_1$ and $\hat{T}_2$ exciting electrons into virtual orbitals.

M.3 Density Functional Approximations

