P.2 Key Equations for Biology

Genetic code: Each codon (3 nucleotides) specifies an amino acid.

Protein translation rate:
v_{\text{translation}} = k_{\text{elong}} [\text{ribosome}]


with typical $k_{\text{elong}} \approx 10$ amino acids/s.

Population growth (Malthusian):
\frac{dN}{dt} = rN

Logistic growth:
\frac{dN}{dt} = rN \left(1 - \frac{N}{K}\right)

Michaelis-Menten (already covered).

Hill equation (cooperativity):
\theta = \frac{[L]^n}{K_d + [L]^n}

Nernst equation (membrane potential):
E = \frac{RT}{zF} \ln \frac{[X]_{\text{out}}}{[X]_{\text{in}}}

Henderson-Hasselbalch equation:
\text{pH} = \text{p}K_a + \log \frac{[A^-]}{[HA]}

P.3 The Central Dogma

\text{DNA} \xrightarrow{\text{transcription}} \text{RNA} \xrightarrow{\text{translation}} \text{Protein}

Transcription rate:
v_{\text{transcription}} = k_{\text{init}} \frac{[RNAP][DNA]}{K_m + [DNA]}

Translation rate: as above.

P.4 Metabolism

Glycolysis net reaction:
\text{Glucose} + 2\text{NAD}^+ + 2\text{ADP} + 2\text{P}_i \rightarrow 2\text{Pyruvate} + 2\text{NADH} + 2\text{ATP} + 2\text{H}_2\text{O}

ATP yield from glucose oxidation: $\approx 30-32$ ATP.

Photosynthesis net reaction:
6\text{CO}_2 + 6\text{H}_2\text{O} + \text{light} \rightarrow \text{C}_6\text{H}_{12}\text{O}_6 + 6\text{O}_2

P.5 Evolution

Fitness $w$: relative reproductive success.

Change in allele frequency (selection):
\Delta p = \frac{p(1-p)(w_{AA} - w_{aa})}{\bar{w}}

Mutation-selection balance:
q \approx \frac{\mu}{s}


for recessive deleterious allele with mutation rate $\mu$ and selection coefficient $s$.

